      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. I want to go deeper than just Locke though. Are there any arguments from a more modern perspective, like regarding digital sovereignty or the idea that the internet is a \"public square\" that shouldn't be governed by any state? I want the arguments to feel really authoritative.",
