    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good direction. I'm trying to make the core case that these arguments aren't just theories, but represent a more logically consistent way to treat human rights in the digital age compared to the current regulatory approach. Do you think these viewpoints are essentially more robust than the standard arguments for government oversight?",
